{
  "texts": [
    "As explained in Sect. 3.2, memorization can be viewed as the influence of a training instance on itself.",
    "Therefore, influence analysis can be used to detect these highly memorized training instances.",
    "These memorized \"bad\" instances are then either removed from the training data or simply relabeled (Kong et al., 2022) and the model retrained.",
    "‖∇ L(z i; (T))‖.",
    "Poisoning and backdoor attacks craft malicious training instances that manipulate a model to align with some attacker objective."
  ]
}